          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Two reactions were used to produce the 7Be beam both",
                "using a 3He gas target. 3He(7Li,7Be)T Q = -0.88 MeV",
                "and 3He(6Li,7Be)D Q = +0.11 MeV. There is a factor 2",
                "in the production rate between these two reactions",
                "the 3He(6Li,7Be)d being the higher. The proton rich",
                "7Be secondary beam has clearly more contaminants",
                "compared to the neutron rich 6He and 8Li and this is",
                "due to the fact that the proton rich beams normally",
                "have lower magnetic rigidity compared to the neutron",
                "rich beams and in general lower than the primary."
              ]
            }
          ],
